Yet more non-creationist, non-ID "critical analysis"?  Yeah, right.  Here we have:

<b>3d. (claim 1):</b> Microevolution is fine, but macroevolution is speculative.  This is decades old, completely standard  creationist code for "We accept microevolution within the specially created 'kinds' of Genesis, but we do not accept 'macroevolution', the evolution of 'new' 'kinds' of organisms."  (This is usually accompanied by the assertion that creationists aren't quite sure what the created kinds are, but they are working real hard on figuring out the boundaries.)  The argument, of course, is <url href="http://www.talkorigins.org/indexcc/list.html#CB900">wrong</url>.

